quran[129]{c,v,t}:
  9,1,"ňĻThis isňļ a discharge from all obligations,¬†by God and His Messenger, to the polytheists you ňĻbelieversňļ have entered into treaties with"
  9,2,"‚ÄúYou ňĻpolytheistsňļ may travel freely through the land for four months, but know that you will have no escape from God, and that God will disgrace the disbelievers.‚ÄĚ"
  9,3,"A declaration from God and His Messenger ňĻis madeňļ to all people on the day of the greater pilgrimage¬†that God and His Messenger are free of the polytheists. So if you ňĻpagansňļ repent, it will be better for you. But if you turn away, then know that you will have no escape from God. And give good news ňĻO Prophetňļ to the disbelievers of a painful punishment"
  9,4,"As for the polytheists who have honoured every term of their treaty with you and have not supported an enemy against you, honour your treaty with them until the end of its term. Surely God loves those who are mindful ňĻof Himňļ"
  9,5,"But once the Sacred Months have passed, kill the polytheists ňĻwho violated their treatiesňļ wherever you find them,¬†capture them, besiege them, and lie in wait for them on every way. But if they repent, perform prayers, and pay alms-tax, then set them free. Indeed, God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,6,"And if anyone from the polytheists asks for your protection ňĻO Prophetňļ, grant it to them so they may hear the Word of God, then escort them to a place of safety, for they are a people who have no knowledge"
  9,7,"How can such polytheists have a treaty with God and His Messenger, except those you have made a treaty with at the Sacred Mosque?¬†So, as long as they are true to you, be true to them. Indeed God loves those who are mindful ňĻof Himňļ"
  9,8,"How ňĻcan they have a treatyňļ? If they were to have the upper hand over you, they would have no respect for kinship or treaty. They only flatter you with their tongues, but their hearts are in denial, and most of them are rebellious"
  9,9,"They chose a fleeting gain over God‚Äôs revelations, hindering ňĻothersňļ from His Way. Evil indeed is what they have done"
  9,10,They do not honour the bonds of kinship or treaties with the believers. It is they who are the transgressors
  9,11,"But if they repent, perform prayer, and pay alms-tax, then they are your brothers in faith. This is how We make the revelations clear for people of knowledge"
  9,12,"But if they break their oaths after making a pledge and attack your faith, then fight the champions of disbelief‚ÄĒwho never honour their oaths‚ÄĒso perhaps they will desist"
  9,13,"Will you not fight those who have broken their oaths, conspired to expel the Messenger ňĻfrom Meccaňļ, and attacked you first? Do you fear them? God is more deserving of your fear, if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  9,14,"ňĻSoňļ fight them and God will punish them at your hands, put them to shame, help you overcome them, and soothe the hearts of the believers‚ÄĒ"
  9,15,"removing rage from their hearts. And God pardons whoever He wills. For God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,16,"Do you ňĻbelieversňļ think that you will be left without God proving who among you ňĻtrulyňļ struggles ňĻin His causeňļ and never takes trusted allies other than God, His Messenger, or the believers? And God is All-Aware of what you do"
  9,17,"It is not for the polytheists to maintain the mosques of God while they openly profess disbelief. Their deeds are void, and they will be in the Fire forever"
  9,18,"The mosques of God should only be maintained by those who believe in God and the Last Day, establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and fear none but God. It is right to hope that they will be among the ňĻtrulyňļ guided"
  9,19,Do you ňĻpagansňļ consider providing the pilgrims with water and maintaining the Sacred Mosque as equal to believing in God and the Last Day and struggling in the cause of God? They are not equal in God‚Äôs sight. And God does not guide the wrongdoing people
  9,20,"Those who have believed, emigrated, and strived in the cause of God with their wealth and their lives are greater in rank in the sight of God. It is they who will triumph"
  9,21,"Their Lord gives them good news of His mercy, pleasure, and Gardens with everlasting bliss"
  9,22,to stay there for ever and ever. Surely with God is a great reward
  9,23,"O believers! Do not take your parents and siblings as trusted allies if they choose disbelief over belief. And whoever of you does so, they are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  9,24,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf your parents and children and siblings and spouses and extended family and the wealth you have acquired and the trade you fear will decline and the homes you cherish‚ÄĒňĻif all theseňļ are more beloved to you than God and His Messenger and struggling in His Way, then wait until God brings about His Will. God does not guide the rebellious people.‚ÄĚ"
  9,25,"Indeed God has given you ňĻbelieversňļ victory on many battlefields, even at the Battle of Šł§unain¬†when you took pride in your great numbers, but they proved of no advantage to you. The earth, despite its vastness, seemed to close in on you, then you turned back in retreat"
  9,26,"Then God sent down His reassurance¬†upon His Messenger and the believers, and sent down forces¬†you could not see, and punished those who disbelieved. Such was the reward of the disbelievers"
  9,27,"Then afterwards God will turn in grace to whoever He wills.¬†And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,28,"O believers! Indeed, the polytheists are ňĻspirituallyňļ impure,¬†so they should not approach the Sacred Mosque after this year.¬†If you fear poverty, God will enrich you out of His bounty, if He wills. Surely, God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,29,"Fight those who do not believe in God and the Last Day, nor comply with what God and His Messenger have forbidden, nor embrace the religion of truth from among those who were given the Scripture,¬†until they pay the tax,¬†willingly submitting, fully humbled"
  9,30,"The Jews say, ‚ÄúEzra is the son of God,‚ÄĚ while the Christians say, ‚ÄúThe Messiah is the son of God.‚ÄĚ Such are their baseless assertions, only parroting the words of earlier disbelievers. May God condemn them! How can they be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  9,31,"They have taken their rabbis and monks as well as the Messiah, son of Mary, as lords besides God,¬†even though they were commanded to worship none but One God. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. Glorified is He above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ"
  9,32,"They wish to extinguish God‚Äôs light¬†with their mouths, but God will only allow His light to be perfected, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  9,33,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ňĻtrueňļ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others, even to the dismay of the polytheists"
  9,34,"O believers! Indeed, many rabbis and monks consume people‚Äôs wealth wrongfully and hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of God. Give good news of a painful torment to those who hoard gold and silver and do not spend it in God‚Äôs cause"
  9,35,"The Day ňĻwill comeňļ when their treasure will be heated up in the Fire of Hell, and their foreheads, sides, and backs branded with it. ňĻIt will be said to them,ňļ ‚ÄúThis is the treasure you hoarded for yourselves. Now taste what you hoarded!‚ÄĚ"
  9,36,"Indeed, the number of months ordained by God is twelve‚ÄĒin God‚Äôs Record¬†since the day He created the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒof which four are sacred. That is the Right Way. So do not wrong one another during these months. And together fight the polytheists as they fight against you together. And know that God is with those mindful ňĻof Himňļ"
  9,37,"Reallocating the sanctity of ňĻtheseňļ months¬†is an increase in disbelief, by which the disbelievers are led ňĻfarňļ astray. They adjust the sanctity one year and uphold it in another, only to maintain the number of months sanctified by God, violating the very months God has made sacred. Their evil deeds have been made appealing to them. And God does not guide the disbelieving people"
  9,38,"O believers! What is the matter with you that when you are asked to march forth in the cause of God, you cling firmly to ňĻyourňļ land?¬†Do you prefer the life of this world over the Hereafter? The enjoyment of this worldly life is insignificant compared to that of the Hereafter"
  9,39,"If you do not march forth, He will afflict you with a painful torment and replace you with other people. You are not harming Him in the least. And God is Most Capable of everything"
  9,40,"ňĻIt does not matterňļ if you ňĻbelieversňļ do not support him, for God did in fact support him when the disbelievers drove him out ňĻof Meccaňļ and he was only one of two. While they both were in the cave, he reassured his companion,¬†‚ÄúDo not worry; God is certainly with us.‚ÄĚ So God sent down His serenity upon the Prophet, supported him with forces you ňĻbelieversňļ did not see, and made the word of the disbelievers lowest, while the Word of God is supreme. And God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  9,41,"ňĻO believers!ňļ March forth whether it is easy or difficult for you, and strive with your wealth and your lives in the cause of God. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  9,42,"Had the gain been within reach and the journey shorter, they would have followed you, but the distance seemed too long for them. And they will swear by God, ‚ÄúHad we been able, we would have certainly joined you.‚ÄĚ They are ruining themselves. And God knows that they are surely lying"
  9,43,May God pardon you ňĻO Prophetňļ! Why did you give them permission ňĻto stay behindňļ before those who told the truth were distinguished from those who were lying
  9,44,Those who believe in God and the Last Day do not ask for exemption from striving with their wealth and their lives. And God has perfect knowledge of those who are mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  9,45,"No one would ask for exemption except those who have no faith in God or the Last Day, and whose hearts are in doubt, so they are torn by their doubts"
  9,46,"Had they ňĻreallyňļ intended to march forth, they would have made preparations for it. But God disliked that they should go, so He let them lag behind, and it was said ňĻto themňļ, ‚ÄúStay with those ňĻhelplessňļ who remain behind.‚ÄĚ"
  9,47,"Had they gone forth with you ňĻbelieversňļ, they would have been nothing but trouble for you, and would have scrambled around, seeking to spread discord in your midst. And some of you would have eagerly listened to them. And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of the wrongdoers"
  9,48,"They had already sought to spread discord before¬†and devised every ňĻpossibleňļ plot against you ňĻO Prophetňļ, until the truth came and God‚Äôs Will prevailed‚ÄĒmuch to their dismay"
  9,49,"There are some of them who say, ‚ÄúExempt me and do not expose me to temptation.‚ÄĚ¬†They have already fallen into temptation. And Hell will surely engulf the disbelievers"
  9,50,"If a blessing befalls you ňĻO Prophetňļ, they grieve, but if a disaster befalls you, they say, ‚ÄúWe took our precaution in advance,‚ÄĚ and turn away, rejoicing"
  9,51,"Say, ‚ÄúNothing will ever befall us except what God has destined for us. He is our Protector.‚ÄĚ So in God let the believers put their trust"
  9,52,"Say, ‚ÄúAre you awaiting anything to befall us except one of the two best things: ňĻvictory or martyrdomňļ? But¬†We are awaiting God to afflict you with torment either from Him or at our hands. So keep waiting! We too are waiting with you.‚ÄĚ"
  9,53,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻWhether youňļ donate willingly or unwillingly, it will never be accepted from you, for you have been a rebellious people.‚ÄĚ"
  9,54,"And what prevented their donations from being accepted is that they have lost faith in God and His Messenger, they never come to prayer except half-heartedly, and they never donate except resentfully"
  9,55,"So let neither their wealth nor children impress you ňĻO Prophetňļ. God only intends to torment them through these things in this worldly life, then their souls will depart while they are disbelievers"
  9,56,"They swear by God that they are part of you, but they are not. They only say so out of fear"
  9,57,"If only they could find a refuge, or a cave, or any hiding-place, they would rush headlong towards it"
  9,58,"There are some of them who are critical of your distribution of alms ňĻO Prophetňļ. If they are given some of it they are pleased, but if not they are enraged"
  9,59,"If only they had been content with what God and His Messenger had given them and said, ‚ÄúGod is sufficient for us! God will grant us out of His bounty, and so will His Messenger. To God ňĻaloneňļ we turn with hope.‚ÄĚ"
  9,60,"Alms-tax is only for the poor and the needy, for those employed to administer it, for those whose hearts are attracted ňĻto the faithňļ, for ňĻfreeingňļ slaves, for those in debt, for God‚Äôs cause, and for ňĻneedyňļ travellers. ňĻThis isňļ an obligation from God. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,61,"And there are others who hurt the Prophet by saying, ‚ÄúHe listens to anyone.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúHe listens to what is best for you. He believes in God, has faith in the believers, and is a mercy for those who believe among you.‚ÄĚ Those who hurt God‚Äôs Messenger will suffer a painful punishment"
  9,62,"They swear by God to you ňĻbelieversňļ in order to please you, while it is the pleasure of God and His Messenger they should seek, if they are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  9,63,Do they not know that whoever opposes God and His Messenger will be in the Fire of Hell forever? That is the ultimate disgrace
  9,64,"The hypocrites fear that a s√Ľrah¬†should be revealed about them, exposing what is in their hearts. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúKeep mocking! God will definitely bring to light what you fear.‚ÄĚ"
  9,65,"If you question them, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúWe were only talking idly and joking around.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúWas it God, His revelations, and His Messenger that you ridiculed?‚ÄĚ"
  9,66,"Make no excuses! You have lost faith after your belief. If We pardon a group of you,¬†We will punish others for their wickedness"
  9,67,"The hypocrites, both men and women, are all alike: they encourage what is evil, forbid what is good, and withhold ňĻwhat is inňļ their hands. They neglected God, so He neglected them. Surely the hypocrites are the rebellious"
  9,68,"God has promised the hypocrites, both men and women, and the disbelievers an everlasting stay in the Fire of Hell‚ÄĒit is sufficient for them. God has condemned them, and they will suffer a never-ending punishment"
  9,69,"ňĻYou hypocrites areňļ like those ňĻdisbelieversňļ before you. They were far superior to you in might and more abundant in wealth and children. They enjoyed their share in this life. You have enjoyed your share, just as they did. And you have engaged in idle talk, just as they did. Their deeds have become void in this world and the Hereafter. And it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ losers"
  9,70,"Have they not received the stories of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them: the people of Noah, ‚Äô√ād, and Tham√Ľd, the people of Abraham, the residents of Midian, and the overturned cities ňĻof Lotňļ?¬†Their messengers came to them with clear proofs. God would have never wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  9,71,"The believers, both men and women, are guardians of one another. They encourage good and forbid evil, establish prayer and pay alms-tax, and obey God and His Messenger. It is they who will be shown God‚Äôs mercy. Surely God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  9,72,"God has promised the believers, both men and women, Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever, and splendid homes in the Gardens of Eternity, and‚ÄĒabove all‚ÄĒthe pleasure of God. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the ultimate triumph"
  9,73,"O Prophet! Struggle against the disbelievers and the hypocrites, and be firm with them. Hell will be their home. What an evil destination"
  9,74,"They swear by God that they never said anything ňĻblasphemousňļ, while they did in fact utter a blasphemy, lost faith after accepting Islam, and plotted what they could not carry out.¬†It is only through resentment that they pay God and His Messenger back for enriching them out of His bounty! If they repent, it will be better for them. But if they turn away, God will torment them with a painful punishment in this world and the Hereafter, and they will have no one on earth to protect or help them"
  9,75,"And there are some who had made a vow to God: ‚ÄúIf He gives us from His bounty, we will surely spend in charity and be of the righteous.‚ÄĚ"
  9,76,"But when He gave them out of His bounty, they withheld it and turned away indifferently"
  9,77,"So He caused hypocrisy to plague their hearts until the Day they will meet Him, for breaking their promise to God and for their lies"
  9,78,"Do they not know that God ňĻfullyňļ knows their ňĻevilňļ thoughts and secret talks, and that God is the Knower of all unseen"
  9,79,"ňĻThere areňļ those who slander ňĻsome ofňļ the believers for donating liberally and mock others for giving only the little they can afford. God will throw their mockery back at them, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  9,80,"ňĻIt does not matterňļ whether you ňĻO Prophetňļ pray for them to be forgiven or not. Even if you pray for their forgiveness seventy times, God will never forgive them. That is because they have lost faith in God and His Messenger. And God does not guide the rebellious people"
  9,81,"Those ňĻhypocritesňļ who remained behind rejoiced for doing so in defiance of the Messenger of God and hated ňĻthe prospect ofňļ striving with their wealth and their lives in the cause of God. They said ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúDo not march forth in the heat.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúThe Fire of Hell is far hotter!‚ÄĚ If only they could comprehend"
  9,82,So let them laugh a little‚ÄĒthey will weep much as a reward for what they have committed
  9,83,"If God returns you ňĻO Prophetňļ to a group of them and they ask to go forth with you, say, ‚ÄúYou will not ever go forth or fight an enemy along with me. You preferred to stay behind the first time, so stay with those ňĻhelplessňļ who remain behind.‚ÄĚ"
  9,84,"And do not ever offer ňĻfuneralňļ prayers for any of their dead, nor stand by their grave ňĻat burialňļ, for they have lost faith in God and His Messenger and died rebellious"
  9,85,"And let neither their wealth nor children impress you ňĻO Prophetňļ. God only intends to torment them through these things in this world, and ňĻthenňļ their souls will depart while they are disbelievers"
  9,86,"Whenever a s√Ľrah¬†is revealed stating, ‚ÄúBelieve in God and struggle along with His Messenger,‚ÄĚ the rich among them would ask to be exempt, saying, ‚ÄúLeave us with those who remain behind.‚ÄĚ"
  9,87,"They preferred to stay behind with the helpless, and their hearts have been sealed so they do not comprehend"
  9,88,"But the Messenger and the believers with him strived with their wealth and their lives. They will have all the best, and it is they who will be successful"
  9,89,"God has prepared for them Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  9,90,"Some nomadic Arabs ňĻalsoňļ came with excuses, seeking exemption. And those who were untrue to God and His Messenger remained behind ňĻwith no excuseňļ. The unfaithful among them will be afflicted with a painful punishment"
  9,91,"There is no blame on the weak, the sick, or those lacking the means ňĻif they stay behindňļ, as long as they are true to God and His Messenger. There is no blame on the good-doers. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,92,"Nor ňĻis there any blame onňļ those who came to you ňĻO Prophetňļ for mounts, then when you said, ‚ÄúI can find no mounts for you,‚ÄĚ they left with eyes overflowing with tears out of grief that they had nothing to contribute"
  9,93,"Blame is only on those who seek exemption from you although they have the means. They preferred to stay behind with the helpless, and God has sealed their hearts so they do not realize ňĻthe consequencesňļ"
  9,94,"They will make excuses to you ňĻbelieversňļ when you return to them. Say, ‚ÄúMake no excuses, ňĻforňļ we will not believe you. God has already informed us about your ňĻtrueňļ state ňĻof faithňļ. Your ňĻfutureňļ deeds will be observed by God and His Messenger as well. And you will be returned to the Knower of the seen and unseen, then He will inform you of what you used to do.‚ÄĚ"
  9,95,"When you return, they will swear to you by God so that you may leave them alone. So leave them alone‚ÄĒthey are truly evil. Hell will be their home as a reward for what they have committed"
  9,96,"They will swear to you in order to please you. And even if you are pleased with them, God will never be pleased with the rebellious people"
  9,97,"The nomadic Arabs ňĻaround Medinaňļ are far worse in disbelief and hypocrisy, and less likely to know the laws revealed by God to His Messenger. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,98,"And among the nomads are those who consider what they donate to be a loss and await your misfortune. May ill-fortune befall them! And God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  9,99,"However, among the nomadic Arabs are those who believe in God and the Last Day, and consider what they donate as a means of coming closer to God and ňĻreceivingňļ the prayers of the Messenger. It will certainly bring them closer. God will admit them into His mercy. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,100,"As for the foremost‚ÄĒthe first of the Emigrants¬†and the Helpers‚ÄĒand those who follow them in goodness, God is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. And He has prepared for them Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  9,101,"Some of the nomads around you ňĻbelieversňļ are hypocrites, as are some of the people of Medina. They have mastered hypocrisy. They are not known to you ňĻO Prophetňļ; they are known to Us. We will punish them twice ňĻin this worldňļ,¬†then they will be brought back ňĻto their Lordňļ for a tremendous punishment"
  9,102,"Some others have confessed their wrongdoing: they have mixed goodness with evil.¬†It is right to hope that God will turn to them in mercy. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,103,"Take from their wealth ňĻO Prophetňļ charity to purify and bless them, and pray for them‚ÄĒsurely your prayer is a source of comfort for them. And God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  9,104,"Do they not know that God alone accepts the repentance of His servants and receives ňĻtheirňļ charity, and that God alone is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  9,105,"Tell ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúDo as you will. Your deeds will be observed by God, His Messenger, and the believers. And you will be returned to the Knower of the seen and unseen, then He will inform you of what you used to do.‚ÄĚ"
  9,106,"And some others are left for God‚Äôs decision, either to punish them or turn to them in mercy.¬†And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,107,"There are also those ňĻhypocritesňļ who set up a mosque ňĻonlyňļ to cause harm, promote disbelief, divide the believers, and as a base for those who had previously fought against God and His Messenger.¬†They will definitely swear, ‚ÄúWe intended nothing but good,‚ÄĚ but God bears witness that they are surely liars"
  9,108,"Do not ňĻO Prophetňļ ever pray in it. Certainly, a mosque founded on righteousness from the first day is more worthy of your prayers. In it are men who love to be purified.¬†And God loves those who purify themselves"
  9,109,"Which is better: those who laid the foundation of their building on the fear and pleasure of God, or those who did so on the edge of a crumbling cliff that tumbled down with them into the Fire of Hell? And God does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  9,110,"The building which they erected will never cease to fuel hypocrisy in their hearts until their hearts are torn apart. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,111,"God has indeed purchased from the believers their lives and wealth in exchange for Paradise. They fight in the cause of God and kill or are killed. This is a true promise binding on Him in the Torah, the Gospel, and the Quran. And whose promise is truer than God‚Äôs? So rejoice in the exchange you have made with Him. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the ultimate triumph"
  9,112,"ňĻIt is the believersňļ who repent, who are devoted to worship, who praise ňĻtheir Lordňļ, who fast, who bow down and prostrate themselves, who encourage good and forbid evil, and who observe the limits set by God. And give good news to the believers"
  9,113,"It is not ňĻproperňļ for the Prophet and the believers to seek forgiveness for the polytheists, even if they were close relatives, after it has become clear to the believers that they are bound for the Hellfire"
  9,114,"As for Abraham‚Äôs prayer for his father‚Äôs forgiveness, it was only in fulfilment of a promise he had made to him. But when it became clear to Abraham that his father was an enemy of God, he broke ties with him.¬†Abraham was truly tender-hearted, forbearing"
  9,115,"God would never consider a people deviant after He has guided them, until He makes clear to them what they must avoid. Surely God has ňĻfullňļ knowledge of everything"
  9,116,"Indeed, to God ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He gives life and causes death. And besides God you have no guardian or helper"
  9,117,"God has certainly turned in mercy to the Prophet¬†as well as the Emigrants and the Helpers who stood by him in the time of hardship, after the hearts of a group of them had almost faltered. He then accepted their repentance. Surely He is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to them"
  9,118,"And ňĻGod has also turned in mercy toňļ the three who had remained behind, ňĻwhose guilt distressed themňļ until the earth, despite its vastness, seemed to close in on them, and their souls were torn in anguish. They knew there was no refuge from God except in Him. Then He turned to them in mercy so that they might repent. Surely God ňĻaloneňļ is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  9,119,O believers! Be mindful of God and be with the truthful
  9,120,"It was not ňĻproperňļ for the people of Medina and the nomadic Arabs around them to avoid marching with the Messenger of God or to prefer their own lives above his. That is because whenever they suffer from thirst, fatigue, or hunger in the cause of God; or tread on a territory, unnerving the disbelievers; or inflict any loss on an enemy‚ÄĒit is written to their credit as a good deed. Surely God never discounts the reward of the good-doers"
  9,121,"And whenever they make a donation, small or large, or cross a valley ňĻin God‚Äôs causeňļ‚ÄĒit is written to their credit, so that God may grant them the best reward for what they used to do"
  9,122,"ňĻHowever,ňļ it is not necessary for the believers to march forth all at once. Only a party from each group should march forth, leaving the rest to gain religious knowledge then enlighten their people when they return to them, so that they ňĻtooňļ may beware ňĻof evilňļ"
  9,123,O believers! Fight the disbelievers around you and let them find firmness in you. And know that God is with those mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  9,124,"Whenever a s√Ľrah¬†is revealed, some of them ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhich of you has this increased in faith?‚ÄĚ As for the believers, it has increased them in faith and they rejoice"
  9,125,"But as for those with sickness in their hearts,¬†it has increased them only in wickedness upon their wickedness, and they die as disbelievers"
  9,126,Do they not see that they are tried once or twice every year?¬†Yet they neither repent nor do they learn a lesson
